relation: U.S. Air Force Space Command (AFSC) formally declared the GPS satellite constellation consisting of 24 GPS satellites (Block I and Block II/IIA) as having met the requirement for Initial Operational Capability (IOC).
The first operational CORS station is NGS-owned station GAIT in Gaithersburg, MD.

The U.S. Air Force Space Command (AFSC) formally declared the GPS satellite constellation as having met the requirement for Full Operational Capability (FOC) as of April 27, 1995. Requirements include 24 operational satellites (Block II/IIA) functioning in their assigned orbits and successful testing completed for operational military functionality.

GNSS observational data from sites are ingested by NGS and are posted to the NGS online servers as daily files in RINEX format (ASCII). The NGDC archive has automated daily routines that selectively pull in the daily observational files at the original sampling rate, the daily observational summary file, the daily broadcast ephemeris files, and any corresponding meteorological files. Each site has a metadata record retained as a site log file (ASCII).
